<subSubSection id="C3116523FFAFA50FCFEBC2DAFB72A59F" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB436A8FFAFA50FCFEBC2DAFCFCA53F" blockId="22.[151,1436,610,1236]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCFEBC2DAFEC3A487" bold="true" box="[198,346,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Description.</emphasis>
Shell large, solid, tall with high gloss. Body whorl narrowly conical, outline straight. Shoul- der narrow, straight angled, slightly concave above and merging into spire. Spire of moderate height, stepped; outline almost straight and sharply pointed. Aperture narrow, parallel, slightly wider posteriorly, anal notch very deep, outer lip sharp, straight; slightly curved anteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436A8FFAFA50FCFEBC37AFB72A59F" blockId="22.[151,1436,610,1236]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ground colour white, heavily covered with dense network of small and medium reddish-brown tents; two rows of dark reddish brown blotches, one above the centre and the other below; blotches are oval and do not tend to form complete spiral bands; blotches contain weakly defined reticulated lines and traces of fine spiral dashes. Spire with similar reddish-dark brown blotches. Spire tip pale pinkish. Aperture white.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3116523FFAFA50FCFEBC39AFE3FA27F" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB436A8FFAFA50FCFEBC39AFADEA22F" blockId="22.[151,1436,610,1236]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCFEBC39AFEC6A5C7" bold="true" box="[198,351,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Distribution.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B59FFAFA50FCE45C39AFD87A5C7" author="Okutani, T." box="[360,542,970,996]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="66 - 69" refId="ref45617" refString="Okutani, T. (1968) A New Cone from the Bay of Bengal, Darioconus bengalensis, n. sp. Venus, 26 (3 &amp; 4), 66 - 69." type="journal article" year="1968">Okutani (1968)</bibRefCitation>
first reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCDEAC39AFCEDA5C0" authorityName="Okutani" authorityYear="1968" box="[711,884,970,995]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Darioconus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCDEAC39AFCEDA5C0" box="[711,884,970,995]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Glory of Bengal) from the Bay of Bengal (as ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCF8CC3A2FE25A228" authorityName="Okutani" authorityYear="1968" box="[161,444,1010,1035]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Darioconus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCF8CC3A2FE25A228" box="[161,444,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Darioconus bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B59FFAFA50FCEF2C3A2FDECA22F" author="Kohn, A. J." box="[479,629,1010,1036]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="357 - 362" refId="ref43801" refString="Kohn, A. J. (2001) The Conidae of India revisited. Phuket Marine Biological Centre Special Publication, 25, 357 - 362." type="journal article" year="2001">Kohn (2001)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCDD1C3A2FC31A228" authorityName="Okutani" authorityYear="1968" box="[764,936,1010,1035]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Darioconus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCDD1C3A2FC31A228" box="[764,936,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was restricted to the Indian Ocean.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436A8FFAFA50FCFEBC44AFE3FA27F" blockId="22.[151,1436,610,1236]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
The specimens reported herein were collected from Mandapam and Keelakarai (
<tableCitation id="C6890313FFAFA50FCBABC44AFB78A217" box="[1158,1249,1050,1076]" captionStart="TABLE 6" captionStartId="12.[151,236,198,220]" captionText="TABLE 6. Presence () of Conus species and total number of species per sampling site." pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Table 6</tableCitation>
) by trawling in 
<quantity id="4CF39B4DFFAFA50FCFBAC412FF67A27F" box="[151,254,1090,1116]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="55.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="50.0">50–60 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity id="4CF39B4DFFAFA50FCE1AC412FE3BA27F" box="[311,418,1090,1116]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="27.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="25.0">25–30 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3116523FFAFA50FCFEBC43AFACFA2F7" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB436A8FFAFA50FCFEBC43AFACFA2F7" blockId="22.[151,1436,610,1236]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCFEBC43AFEA0A2A7" bold="true" box="[198,313,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B59FFAFA50FCE6EC43AFDAFA2A7" author="Rockel, D. &amp; Korn, W. &amp; Kohn, A. J." box="[323,566,1130,1156]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="84" refId="ref46330" refString="Rockel, D., Korn, W. &amp; Kohn, A. J. (1995) Manual of the living Conidae. Vol. 1: Indo-Pacific. Christa Hemmen Verlag, Wiesbaden, pp. 516, pl. 84." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Röckel 
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCE8DC43BFE44A2A7" box="[416,477,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
(1995)
</bibRefCitation>
observed that the shells of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCCABC43BFBACA2A7" authorityName="Okutani" authorityYear="1968" box="[902,1077,1131,1156]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Darioconus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCCABC43BFBACA2A7" box="[902,1077,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southeast 
<collectingCountry id="F31C7638FFAFA50FCBD7C43AFAAFA2A7" box="[1274,1334,1130,1156]" name="India" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">India</collectingCountry>
differed from typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCE1FC4C3FE79A28F" authorityName="Okutani" authorityYear="1968" box="[306,480,1171,1196]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Darioconus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCE1FC4C3FE79A28F" box="[306,480,1171,1196]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">C. bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a broader body whorl. However, the specimens from Gulf of Mannar had comparatively narrowly conical body whorl. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D2BFFAFA50FCDF4C4EBFC2FA2F7" baseAuthorityName="Okutani" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[729,950,1211,1236]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bengalensis">
<emphasis id="B97FEABAFFAFA50FCDF4C4EBFC2FA2F7" box="[729,950,1211,1236]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Conus bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rare along the 
<collectingRegion id="49CFF84AFFAFA50FCBADC4EAFA9AA2F7" box="[1152,1283,1210,1236]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">TamilNadu</collectingRegion>
Coast.
</paragraph>
